Cities & Localities in Taylor County, FL

Perry (county seat)

Steinhatchee

Taylor County is located in North Central Region in the Panhandle bordering the Gulf of Mexico and Jefferson, Madison, Lafayette and Dixie Counties.

Taylor County was established from a portion of Madison County in 1856 and named for Zachary Taylor, Commander of the Federal forces during the Second Seminole War and 12th President of the U.S.
